data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression tree no longer compiles

EF Core 10 added a new **non-expression** `Func<>` overload. Your manual expression-tree code won't compile because the compiler now prefers the simpler overload. The fix is to **delete all that expression-tree plumbing** and use the new lambda syntax:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — two breaking changes

**a) Shared column names are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column, EF 10 will generate `Street` and `Street1`. To keep the old mapping, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City` — now it becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update all other methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
